<subSubSection id="C95E49A767AB695BE8163DBB67781E18" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="4EFD59DA79B5F09DE59B18AB50F51820" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DAD45894E5BEBC4A82E69F6E3899D6B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A relatively distinct cerrado species with the characteristically shortly petiolate leaves of an erect or ascending species. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="880C3EEBBC04C513BA5C902582E3F311" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
<emphasis id="31301F8A5CB4E5CDE8DFA2ED55F3D3E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea hirsutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DB2BDD2E0B9EAA6833BE6F6037DA3A35" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aurifera">
<emphasis id="7F0B5DED08C169B14BA6F6E2DFF5973E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. aurifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in habit but is distinguished by the pubescent indumentum, ovate leaves and sepals, and shortly pedicellate white flowers borne in small axillary cymes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1042EFCFFB1A61D5832D16FAD65863A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The 
<normalizedToken id="0C9E6263E84F01A70C6DC25B30E542A9" originalValue="Rondônia">Rondonia</normalizedToken>
collection, 
<emphasis id="5E20DEA6EA805C4CC8EF08C7D0B12C51" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Veira et al.</emphasis>
783, is somewhat anomalous having slightly larger sepals and pink flowers (according to the collection label). In habit and other details it fits 
<taxonomicName id="7AA96A9A382396B3726098B7432AE436" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cerradoensis">
<emphasis id="0D8C23BFE6B4D7893A85FF6340FE7258" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea cerradoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is probably correctly placed here unless further collections from 
<normalizedToken id="672D07100412626B6E683F28A725F53E" originalValue="Rondônia">Rondonia</normalizedToken>
prove otherwise.
</paragraph>
